    <A NAME="ccRef_CGAL::Memory_sizer"></A>
<h2><I>CGAL::Memory_sizer</I></h2>
<P>

<H3>Definition</H3>
<P>

The class <I><A HREF="Class_Memory_sizer.html#Cross_link_anchor_1714">Memory_sizer</A></I> allows to measure the memory size used by the process.
Both the virtual memory size and the resident size are available (the resident
size does not account for swapped out memory nor for the memory which is not
yet paged-in).
<P>

<I>#include &lt;<A HREF="../../../include/CGAL/Memory_sizer.h">CGAL/Memory_sizer.h</A>&gt;</I>
<P>

<H3>Types</H3>
<P>

The memory sizes are given in bytes.
